'''Dhyan network management system''' (DNMS) is [[carrier grade]] [[network management system]] providing generic [[topology]], fault, configuration, performance, and security ([[FCAPS]]) functions. It provides the major functions for deploying, monitoring, configuring and managing a network.

==Flexibility==
Since DNMS is [[modular]], it can be easily customized and extended.{{Citation needed|date=October 2011}} DNMS has been deployed to manage different types of networks and [[network element]]s whether it is [[wireless access point]]s, or [[optical switch]]es or [[core router]]s.{{Citation needed|date=October 2011}}

==Interfaces==
DNMS supports a variety of [[Northbound interface|northbound and southbound interfaces]].

Northbound interfaces are provided to pass information to other network management and [[service management systems]] using [[Java Management Extensions|JMX]], [[CORBA]], [[SNMP]] and [[XML]]/[[HTTP]] protocols.

Southbound interfaces provide two-way access to network elements using any proprietary protocols required by the customer as well as standard protocols, such as SNMP, [[TL1]], XML, [[Common management information protocol|CMIP]], CORBA and [[NetFlow]]/[[IPFIX]].

